<tmc-service-inc>
<pub id="RM21Q3EV">
<servcat id="43">
<name>BODY</name>
<section id="1002V_S0014" variety="S0014">
<name>MIRROR</name>
<ttl id="1002V_S0014_7ARMA_T009M" variety="T009M">
<name>OUTER MIRROR COVER</name>
<para id="RM000004RUS00VX" category="A" type-id="80001" name-id="MX2SX-05" from="201403">
<name>REMOVAL</name>
<subpara id="RM000004RUS00VX_02" type-id="11" category="10" proc-id="RM21Q0EV__000046200001">
<content3 releasenbr="1">
<atten4>
<list1 type="unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>Use the same procedure for the RH and LH sides.</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>The procedure listed below is for the LH side.</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</atten4>
</content3>
</subpara>
<subpara id="RM000004RUS00VX_01" type-id="01" category="01">
<s-1 id="RM000004RUS00VX_01_0004" proc-id="RM21Q0EV__000046000001">
<ptxt>REMOVE OUTER REAR VIEW MIRROR ASSEMBLY LH (w/ Side Turn Signal Light)</ptxt>
<content1 releasenbr="1">
<ptxt>(See page <xref label="Seep01" href="RM0000015DU048X"/>)</ptxt>
</content1>
</s-1>
<s-1 id="RM000004RUS00VX_01_0001" proc-id="RM21Q0EV__000045S00000">
<ptxt>REMOVE OUTER MIRROR LH
</ptxt>
<content1 releasenbr="1">
<s2>
<ptxt>Using a screwdriver with its tip, detach the 2 claws as shown in the illustration.</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="B278386E01" width="7.106578999in" height="3.779676365in"/>
</figure>
<table pgwide="1">
<title>Text in Illustration</title>
<tgroup cols="4">
<colspec colname="COL1" align="left" colwidth="0.71in"/>
<colspec colname="COL2" colwidth="2.83in"/>
<colspec colname="COL3" align="left" colwidth="0.71in"/>
<colspec colname="COL4" colwidth="2.83in"/>
<tbody>
<row>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>*1</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>Screw Driver</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>*2</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>Protective Tape</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
<atten3>
<ptxt>Do not pull the outer mirror LH with excessive force. Doing so may cause the actuator to come off or break the mirror surface.</ptxt>
</atten3>
<atten4>
<ptxt>Apply protective tape to the mirror body and screw driver.</ptxt>
</atten4>
</s2>
<s2>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="B278387" width="2.775699831in" height="2.775699831in"/>
</figure>
<ptxt>Detach the 2 claws at the upper part of the outer mirror.</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>Remove the outer mirror LH.</ptxt>
</s2>
</content1></s-1>
<s-1 id="RM000004RUS00VX_01_0002" proc-id="RM21Q0EV__000045Z00001">
<ptxt>REMOVE OUTER MIRROR COVER LH (w/ Side Turn Signal Light)</ptxt>
<content1 releasenbr="1">
<s2>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="B278447E01" width="2.775699831in" height="1.771723296in"/>
</figure>
<ptxt>Remove the tape.</ptxt>
<table>
<title>Text in Illustration</title>
<tgroup cols="2">
<colspec colname="COL1" colwidth="0.41in"/>
<colspec colname="COL2" colwidth="3.72in"/>
<tbody>
<row>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>*1</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry>
<ptxt>Tape</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</s2>
<s2>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="B280806" width="2.775699831in" height="1.771723296in"/>
</figure>
<ptxt>Remove the screw, detach the 10 claws and remove the rubber base.</ptxt>
<atten4>
<ptxt>It is not necessary to completely remove the rubber base. Slightly more the rubber base so that the outer mirror cover LH can be removed in a later step.</ptxt>
</atten4>
</s2>
<s2>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="B278380" width="2.775699831in" height="1.771723296in"/>
</figure>
<ptxt>Using a T25 "TORX" socket wrench, remove the 3 screws.</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="B278382" width="2.775699831in" height="3.779676365in"/>
</figure>
<ptxt>Remove the 3 screws.</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="B280813" width="2.775699831in" height="1.771723296in"/>
</figure>
<ptxt>Using a screwdriver, detach the 6 claws.</ptxt>
<atten4>
<ptxt>Tape the screwdriver tip before use.</ptxt>
</atten4>
</s2>
<s2>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="B280814" width="2.775699831in" height="1.771723296in"/>
</figure>
<ptxt> Detach the 2 claws and remove the outer mirror cover LH as shown in the illustration.</ptxt>
</s2>
</content1>
</s-1>
<s-1 id="RM000004RUS00VX_01_0005" proc-id="RM21Q0EV__000046100001">
<ptxt>REMOVE OUTER MIRROR COVER LH (w/o Side Turn Signal Light)</ptxt>
<content1 releasenbr="1">
<s2>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="B280810E01" width="2.775699831in" height="1.771723296in"/>
</figure>
<ptxt>Using a screwdriver, detach the 6 claws.</ptxt>
<atten4>
<ptxt>Tape the screwdriver tip before use.</ptxt>
</atten4>
</s2>
<s2>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="B280807E01" width="2.775699831in" height="2.775699831in"/>
</figure>
<ptxt>Detach the 3 claws as shown in the illustration and remove the outer mirror cover LH.</ptxt>
</s2>
</content1>
</s-1>
</subpara>
</para>
</ttl>
</section>
